Source: qmail-run
Section: mail
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Gerrit Pape <pape@smarden.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 3.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.5.2

Package: qmail-run
Architecture: any
Depends: qmail (>> 1.03-woody0), daemontools (>= 0.76-1), ucspi-tcp (>> 0.88-woody0), procmail
Suggests: mail-reader
Conflicts: mail-transport-agent
Replaces: mail-transport-agent, qmail (<< 1.03-woody0)
Provides: mail-transport-agent
Description: sets up qmail as mail-transfer-agent
 This package sets up the debian var-qmail installation as
 mail-transfer-agent. It follows the most commonly used public documentation
 http://www.lifewithqmail.org almost completely and does the same a user
 would do when installing qmail following the instructions in
 /usr/share/doc/qmail/fastforward/ALIASES and /usr/share/doc/qmail/INSTALL
 starting at step 9.
 .
 See /usr/share/doc/qmail-run/README.Debian for details.
 .
 See http://innominate.org/~pape/Debian/qmail-run.html for more information
 and related packages.
